+
+Examples:
+
+- hype
+- crypto
+- futuristic gimmicks
+- startup marketing
+- artificial urgency
+- AI buzzwords
+
+# Writing Style
+
+Describe how every page should be written.
+
+Cover:
+
+- sentence length
+- tone
+- technical depth
+- use of jargon
+- use of marketing language
+
+# Visual Principles
+
+Describe:
+
+- typography
+- whitespace
+- color philosophy
+- iconography
+- diagrams
+- illustrations
+- animation
+- imagery
+
+Do not specify implementation details.
+
+Describe principles.
+
+# Homepage Philosophy
+
+Explain the purpose of the homepage.
+
+Describe the narrative journey.
+
+Mission
+
+↓
+
+Architecture
+
+↓
+
+Progress
+
+↓
+
+Contribution
+
+Explain why that order exists.
+
+# Long-term Consistency
+
+Explain how future contributors and AI agents should evaluate whether a design change aligns with Public Intelligence.
+
+The document should read like an internal design handbook for an organization that expects to exist for decades.
+
+Do not discuss React, CSS, Tailwind, or implementation.
+
+Focus only on timeless design principles.
+
+Do not modify any other files.
